data.name: accept_lang
data.description: set to your preferred Accept-Language header string

data.name: auth_pass
data.description: specify password used to access password-protected site

data.name: auth_user
data.description: specify username used to access password-protected site

data.name: author
data.description: specify a PDF document author name of max. 150 characters

data.name: creator
data.description: specify a PDF document creator name of max. 150 characters

data.name: css_url
data.description: inject a custom CSS stylesheet using a (urlencoded) URL

data.name: custom_unit
data.description: set to px (Pixels), pt (Points), in (Inches) or mm (Millimeters)

data.name: delay
data.description: specify a delay (in seconds) before PDF is captured

data.name: document_name
data.description: specify a PDF name of up to 180 characters.

data.name: document_url
data.description: The URL of the HTML source you would like to convert to PDF. Looking to use pass raw HTML code to the API? Learn more at https://pdflayer.com/documentation#quickstart

data.name: dpi
data.description: specify the DPI resolution (numerical) between 10 and 10000

data.name: encryption
data.description: set to 40 (40-bit) or 128 (128-bit)

data.name: footer_align
data.description: set to left, center or right

data.name: footer_spacing
data.description: set to preferred footer spacing value (numeric), e.g. 10

data.name: footer_text
data.description: set to preferred footer text, e.g. "This is my footer"

data.name: footer_url
data.description: set to (urlencoded) URL containing your preferred footer HTML elements. Want to use raw HTML code? Learn more at https://pdflayer.com/documentation#pdf_footer

data.name: force
data.description: set to 1 to force new PDF

data.name: forms
data.description: Set to 1 in order to enable forms on your PDF

data.name: grayscale
data.description: Set to 1 in order to remove all colours

data.name: header_align
data.description: set to left, center or right

data.name: header_spacing
data.description: set to preferred header spacing value (numeric), e.g. 10

data.name: header_text
data.description: set to preferred header text, e.g. "This is my heading"

data.name: header_url
data.description: set to (urlencoded) URL containing your preferred header HTML elements. Want to use raw HTML code? Learn more at https://pdflayer.com/documentation#pdf_header

data.name: inline
data.description: set to 1 to display PDF document inline

data.name: low_quality
data.description: Set to 1 in order to generate low quality PDF

data.name: margin_bottom
data.description: set to preferred bottom margin value (numeric), e.g. 5

data.name: margin_left
data.description: set to preferred left margin value (numeric), e.g. 5

data.name: margin_right
data.description: set to preferred right margin value (numeric), e.g. 5

data.name: margin_top
data.description: set to preferred top margin value (numeric), e.g. 5

data.name: no_backgrounds
data.description: Set to 1 in order to disable CSS backgrounds

data.name: no_copy
data.description: Set to 1 in order to disable the possibility to copy any text of the final PDF document. Requires encryption, owner_password or user_password to be specified

data.name: no_hyperlinks
data.description: Set to 1 in order to disable hyperlinks

data.name: no_images
data.description: Set to 1 in order to disable images

data.name: no_javascript
data.description: Set to 1 in order to disable JavaScript

data.name: no_modify
data.description: Set to 1 in order to disable modification of the final PDF document. Requires encryption, owner_password or user_password to be specified

data.name: no_print
data.description: Set to 1 in order to disable printing of the final PDF document. Requires encryption, owner_password or user_password to be specified

data.name: orientation
data.description: set to portrait or landscape

data.name: owner_password
data.description: specify owner password to password protect PDF

data.name: page_height
data.description: specify page height (numeric), e.g. 600 (overrides page_size)

data.name: page_size
data.description: set to preferred page size, e.g. A4, A5, etc.

data.name: page_width
data.description: specify page width (numeric), e.g. 200 (overrides page_size)

data.name: subject
data.description: specify a PDF document subject of max. 150 characters

data.name: text_encoding
data.description: set to your preferred text encoding string

data.name: title
data.description: specify a PDF document title of max. 150 characters

data.name: ttl
data.description: the time (in seconds) a generated PDF is cached

data.name: use_print_media
data.description: Set to 1 in order to activate CSS @media print declarations

data.name: user_agent
data.description: set to your preferred User-Agent header string

data.name: user_password
data.description: specify user password to password protect PDF

data.name: viewport
data.description: Set to preferred viewport "width x height", e.g. 320x480

data.name: watermark_in_background

data.name: watermark_offset_x
data.description: specify a horizontal watermark offset, e.g. 10

data.name: watermark_offset_y
data.description: specify a vertical watermark offset, e.g. 10

data.name: watermark_opacity
data.description: specify watermark opacity percentage (numeric) between 0 and 100

data.name: watermark_url
data.description: specify a watermark URL (urlencoded) containing a PNG or JPG image
